snippet.textDisplay:
The #1 way people consume estrogen in North America is from dairy milk and meat. Soy milk contains phyto-estrogen (phyto meaning plant) and doesn't negatively affect humans. Dairy, however, is mammalian estrogen.
Men who eat and drink soy in place of dairy and meat have lower rates of estrogen, lower cancer-causing IGF-1, and 13% higher testosterone.
The majority of people in the world (over 60%) are some level of lactose intolerant because we do not need the enzyme after infancy (for our mothers).

"It's not harmful for the majority of the population" except 65% of the world are intolerant? So I'm guessing you mean "majority of the population who are lactose tolerant"?
Also, there's even dairy-industry-funded meta analyses that found 50% of studies show an increased risk of prostate cancer, DOI: 10.1136/bmjopen-2018-023625. And you compared the protein levels to plant milk, but didn't mention daily protein needs (~0.8g/kg body weight for idle adults, ~2g per/kg for elite athletes during maximum muscle-growth) and if the protein in dairy is actually needed to meet that need. And plant milk is not that good if you're optimizing for health anyway, so better stick to the whole-food alternatives you mentioned earlier.

snippet.textDisplay:
After checking the sources : Saying that we can find argument against or in favor milk regarding its effect on bones isn't equivalent of no risk left.
In other words, just because some studies say it's "trendiing toward something useful (calcium)" doesn't mean the warnings are to be ignored.
Especially when the core problematic isnt even adressed in the sources in favor of milk.
Also the hormonal impact which is an important one wasnt mentionned.

We know that milk weakens bones and tend to mess up hormonal system, I used to think this channel was delivering more trustworthy information :/

snippet.textDisplay:
Personally, I don't drink milk from animals anymore, I don't see the point.
It's not justifiable to consume the milk of another being if it wasn't meant for you. Cow's milk is for their calves, not for us. Same goes for any other milk that's produced by animals. Why don't you all drink human milk?
Sure, plant milk tastes slightly different and vegan milk products like cheese or yoghurt are different from what most of us grew up with, but let's be honest, I can take never eating milk products ever again, but I can't put up with exploiting animals that are treated like products, like *things*.
